# gcovr -- generate GCC code coverage reports
# Gcovr provides a utility for managing the use of the GNU gcov utility and generating summarized code coverage results. 
# This command is inspired by the Python coverage.py package, which provides a similar utility for Python.

# source code: https://github.com/gcovr/gcovr/
# docs: https://gcovr.com/en/stable/guide.html
# install GCOVR
# $ pip install gcovr

How to use.
Run script:
   ~/facelift/build$ tests/coverage/test_gcovr.sh
Results of test-cases will be available in the folder
   ~/facelift/build$ gcovr/report_gcovr_yy-mm-dd-hms
